citations:
    citation-agot-eddard-xvi:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Eddard XVI"
            text_from_source: "There was no window, no bed, not even a slop bucket … 'Peace,' Varys replied without hesitation. 'If there was one soul in King's Landing who was truly desperate to keep Robert Baratheon alive, it was me.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Ned Stark imprisoned in the black cells beneath the Red Keep. Varys visits in disguise as a turnkey, bringing wine and information. Varys reveals: Arya escaped (whereabouts unknown); Sansa is held and pleaded for Ned's life; Ned is to confess, command Robb to lay down arms, and take the black, in exchange for his life. Cersei plans to grant him the Wall. Varys confirms Lancel Lannister gave Robert the wine (on Cersei's orders) that kept him drunk so he couldn't control the boar. Varys threatens Sansa's life to coerce Ned. Ned recalls the Tourney at Harrenhal: Rhaegar's defeat of Barristan Selmy in the final tilt, and Rhaegar laying blue roses in Lyanna's lap."
